    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-01-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="27"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Haentjens</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-01-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 12th instant, setting forth the grounds upon which your
                    Government acted in expelling the American citizen, Eugene Wiener.</p>
                <p>I have transmitted to oar minister at Port au Prince a copy, explaining that its
                    statements had been verified by evidence submitted by you to this Department,
                    and instructing him to refrain from remonstrance against the expulsion of Mr.
                    Wiener.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
